---
description: VoxMesh core development contract — always applies
alwaysApply: true
---

- Read `AGENTS.md` before making changes; it is the primary development contract. Architecture
  invariants there require a superseding ADR to violate — do not work around them locally.
- Work in small, testable vertical slices tied to a GitHub issue. Branch names:
  `<type>/<issue>-<slug>` (e.g. `feat/123-wasapi-loopback`).
- Pin exact dependency versions; never use floating versions like `latest`.
- Never commit `CMakeUserPresets.json`, secrets, recordings, or transcript data (including in
  fixtures and prompts).
- Never log audio, transcript text, participant names, or tokens.
- If a missing decision blocks correct implementation, stop and ask; otherwise take the safest
  default and document the assumption in the PR.
